HEADWORD: Savageness
<hw>Sav"age*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of being
savage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wolves and bears, they say,⟦br⟧
Casting their <qex>savageness</qex> aside have done⟦br⟧
Like offices of pity.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

